title: St. Francis' Bullough eyes defending state title
text:
St. Francis' Bullough eyes defending state title Posted: JoeBuczek@9and10news.com 
TRAVERSE CITY – Traverse City St. Francis cross country senior Holly Bullough is making sure her prep career ends in an impressive fashion. 
Bullough, who claimed a Division 3 individual state championship at last year’s state finals and finished second and third, respectively, at the 2012 and 2013 Division 4 meets, recently became the fastest female runner in the state, setting a time of 17:16 at a competition at Buckley last month. 
“I felt that I was going at a good pace, but when I finished and heard 17:16, I was like, 'was I really going that fast,’” said Bullough, who committed to Michigan State. 
Bullough and her top-ranked St. Francis team are eyeing an even better showing at next month’s Division 3 state championship, as the Gladiators go for their first state title since 2003. 
St. Francis competes at a Division 3 regional at Gaylord on Oct. 31. Most Popular Stories Most Popular Stories More>>
